cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is about improving the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) by addressing the issue of inhibited channels. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel neural building block, which involves designing a new layer for CNNs, making it likely to also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the theoretical connection between the proposed method and Nash Equilibrium, which suggests a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on various benchmarks, including ImageNet and COCO, indicating a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
